1. Create repository from platform's interface (GitHub, Bitbucket, GitLab)

2. Navigate to directory where you want to create repo
#cd dir

3. Initialise a new Git repository using the following command
#git init

4. Configure username and email address
#git config --global user.name shubham
#git config --global user.email shubham@gmail.com

5. Once you have a remote repository, add it as a remote to your local repository using the git remote add command. Replace <remote-name> with a name for your remote (e.g., "notes"), and <remote-url> with the URL of your remote repository
#git remote add <remote-name> <remote-url>
#git remote add xyz https://github.com/abc/xyz.git

6. Pull code from github first
#git pull https://github.com/abc/xyz.git

7. Verify
#git config --list

8. Add/Create files(code)

9. Add files to staging area
#git add .              // . specifies current directory 

10. Commit the code to local repository
#git commit -m initial_commit               // -m is commit message

11. Push the code to central repository
#git push -u notes main                 //main specifies the branch